<HEADLINE>
FT  04 APR 92 / World Stock Markets (America): Dow defies jobs data to post
modest gains
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Wall Street
AFTER threatening in the morning to break below a key support level for the
Dow index, US stock markets defied disappointing employment news to end the
day with modest gains, writes Patrick Harverson in New York.
At the close the Dow was up 14.99 at 3,249.11, having been more than 20
points down at midday. The more broadly based Standard &amp; Poor's 500 staged a
similar turnaround, finishing up 1.06 at 401.56. The Nasdaq composite index
of over-the-counter stocks, however, fell 3.81 to 590.01. Turnover was 189m
shares.
The keenly awaited March employment report showed a 19,000 rise in non-farm
payrolls and a 34 per cent downward revision in the initially estimated
164,000 rise in February payrolls.
Although the civilian unemployment rate was unchanged at 7.3 per cent last
month, the data overall were a blow to hopes that the economic recovery was
well under way.
Disappointment at the jobs news unleashed immediate selling, and pushed the
Dow near to 3,200 at midday. The morning's declines created buying
opportunities, however, and the market rebounded in the afternoon with most
of the gains coming in the final hour.
The employment data were welcomed by the Treasury markets and in late
trading the benchmark 30-year government bond was up  7/16 at 101 7/16 ,
yielding 7.867 per cent, and the two-year note was up  7/32 at 100, yielding
5.363 per cent.
CMS Energy eased another Dollars  1/8 to Dollars 15 5/8 in turnover of 3.7m
shares after Michigan regulators rejected a proposal on how much the
company's consumer power unit should pay for electricity from a power
generation venture half-owned by CMS.
Broking stocks remained under pressure on fears that the recent boom in
stock and bond offerings was over.
Merrill Lynch fell Dollars 1 1/2 to Dollars 51, PaineWebber lost Dollars
7/8 to Dollars 19 1/8 and AG Edwards slipped Dollars  3/4 to Dollars 22 7/8
.
Canada
TORONTO stocks closed lower in moderate volume of 26.25m shares, the 300
composite index falling 10.43 to 3385.48.
