FT  04 APR 92 / Election 1992: Tory doctors - Ballot Box
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Perhaps surprisingly, given everything that you read, the Tories are still
the favourite political party of the family doctors. According to a poll in
today's Pulse, the weekly magazine for GPs, 29.8 per cent of them say that
they will vote Conservative on Thursday. That compares with 24.8 per cent
for the Liberal Democrats and only 17.8 per cent for the Labour party.
On the other hand, more than 45 per cent of the doctors said they had voted
Tory in 1987. Still, 52 per cent of them favour Tory tax policies.
