<HEADLINE>
FT  04 APR 92 / Standard on currency criticised
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SUPPORT is widespread for the overhaul of accounting standard SSAP20 dealing
with foreign currency translation, according to a survey conducted by the
Chartered Association of Certified Accountants.
In a study of 32 companies, institutions, accounting firms and individuals
conducted for the Accounting Standards Board, the association found that
most organisations wanted disclosure in the accounts of any limitations on
the extent to which overseas assets can be remitted to the UK. That has been
prompted by the experience of Polly Peck International.
Many of those surveyed wanted clarification of reserve accounting, the
treatment of complex capital instruments, and hedging transactions.
