</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SOUTH AFRICA'S President F W de Klerk is expected to visit Nigeria next
week, in a breakthrough in Pretoria's diplomatic relations with black
Africa.
President Ibrahim Babangida, Nigeria's military leader and chairman of the
Organisation of African Unity (OAU), will hold talks with Mr de Klerk in the
capital, Abuja.
Although Mr de Klerk has visited several African countries since initiating
his reform programme, the visit to Nigeria has special significance.
President Babangida's invitation represents a stamp of approval for the
reform process from black Africa's economic and political heavyweight. The
invitation also brings closer the day South Africa becomes a member of the
OAU, given President Babangida's role as chairman of the organisation.
