<DATE>920404
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  04 APR 92 / Finance &amp; The Family Insurance and divorce  - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There could, alas, be strong demand for a new product from DBS Assured
Services. Its Maintenance Protection Plan allows a woman to insure the life
of her ex-husband, even without his knowledge or consent. As life insurance
is rarely high on people's minds amid the acrimony of a divorce, any joint
protection plans a couple may have taken out often lapse. The policy is
underwritten at Lloyd's, and the protection costs Pounds 4.50 for every
Pounds 1,000 sum assured.
</TEXT>
