<DOCNO>FT922-14801</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-CDEAFABHFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>920404
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  04 APR 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
White pepper was available at USDollars 1,300 a tonne and the shipment price
for April/May delivery was Dollars 1,275 a tonne cif. We do not foresee
drastic changes in the near future. The undertone of the black pepper market
was easier because of the growing selling pressure from the Far East
(Malaysia and Vietnam). The spot European price for grade 1 black pepper was
Dollars 1,175 a tonne, while that quality could be obtained on shipment
basis at about Dollars 1,100 a tonne cif.
</TEXT>
