FT  04 APR 92 / UK Company News: M&amp;G buys 11% of Recovery income shares
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Trading in shares in the M&amp;G Recovery Investment Trust started yesterday
afternoon.
By the close of trading, the M&amp;G Group held 14.482m income shares,
equivalent to 11.16 per cent of the total income shares on issue. M&amp;G
Securities, a wholly owned subsidiary of the company, accounted for 12.882m
of these shares.
The company said this represented confidence by its fund managers that the
shares were a 'good buy', and that they would make a suitable home for part
of the company's reserves.
M&amp;G's purchases helped stabilise the income shares which had a turbulent day
on the market, opening on 35p, falling to 34 1/2 p but then recovering to
35p.
Private investors, at whom the launch was targeted, mostly held packaged
units including income shares, zero dividend preference shares, and capital
shares. The packaged units, priced at 100p, closed at 97p.
