House, the developer, says it is the largest office pre-let on a UK business
park.
About 550 Sony staff will relocate to the building at the end of next year.
Sony UK said it had taken two years to pick its new location from a variety
of options in west and southwest London.
Trafalgar House also said it was buying British Aerospace's 50 per cent
interest in the joint venture company set up in 1987 to develop the site. It
did not disclose the price.
