FT  03 APR 92 / Business journal planned
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GARY MEAD, Marketing Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Economist Group yesterday announced that it had reached agreement with
Diamond Incorporated to launch jointly a Japanese-language magazine early
next year.
Global Business magazine will be aimed at internationally minded Japanese
business executives. It will have an initial circulation of some 15,000 and
be published every two weeks.
The magazine's content will split three ways. One third will be translations
of articles from The Economist magazine and another third will cover
international business and finance. The final section will focus on domestic
Japanese issues.
Pearson, publisher of the Financial Times, owns 50 per cent of The
Economist.
Mr David Gordon, chief executive of Economist Group, said the main
publishing risk would be shouldered by Diamond, which already publishes
Japanese-language versions of the Harvard Business Review and Fortune
magazine.
