   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NUMBER of companies passing into administration and receivership during
the first three months of this year in England, Wales and Scotland held at
the same level as last year, figures from Touche Ross showed yesterday.
Insolvency practitioners were appointed administrators and administrative
receivers to 1,559 companies in January to March 1992 compared with 1,563 in
the same period last year. The analysis is based on appointments published
in the monthly London and Edinburgh Gazettes, the official guides to
appointments.
For March this year the total was 527 companies, down slightly from 574 in
the same month last year. Partners from Coopers &amp; Lybrand were appointed
most often as insolvency practitioners, with 110 of the total.
