<TEXT>
SHARES that might benefit from a Tory victory have dropped close to 10 per
cent over the election campaign. Possible 'Labour gainers' are 3 per cent
down.
The big losers among Conservative stocks yesterday were SG Warburg, the
investment bank, down 8p to 463p; and Whitbread, the brewer, down 8p to
386p.
The big loser on the Labour side was ICI, down 15p to 1,224p.
