President Carlos Andres Perez, reports Joe Mann in Caracas.
The president named, late on Wednesday, Ms Ruth de Krivoy, a respected
economist and the first woman to hold the job, to head the central bank.
Mr Rodriguez, who only took the post in late February, was the main
architect of the highly unpopular economic reform programme the Perez
government initiated three years ago.
